Essential Windows Shortcuts for Professional Programmers
=================================================

Line Navigation
--------------
• Home                   - Start of line
• End                    - End of line  
• Ctrl + Home           - Start of document
• Ctrl + End            - End of document

Word Navigation
--------------
• Ctrl + Left/Right     - Jump word by word
• Ctrl + Shift + L/R    - Select word by word
• Ctrl + D              - Select entire word under cursor
• Ctrl + L              - Select entire line

Efficient Editing
----------------
• Ctrl + Backspace      - Delete word to left
• Ctrl + Delete         - Delete word to right
• Ctrl + Shift + K      - Delete entire line
• Ctrl + X              - Cut entire line (no selection needed)
• Ctrl + C              - Copy entire line (no selection needed)
• Alt + Up/Down         - Move line up/down
• Alt + Shift + Up/Down - Duplicate line

Multi-cursor & Selection
-----------------------
• Ctrl + Alt + Up/Down  - Add cursor above/below
• Ctrl + D              - Select next occurrence (press multiple times)
• Ctrl + Shift + L      - Select all occurrences
• Alt + Shift + drag    - Column (box) selection
• Alt + Click           - Add cursor at mouse position

Code Navigation
--------------
• F12                   - Go to definition
• Alt + F12             - Peek definition
• Alt + Left Arrow      - Go back to previous position
• Alt + Right Arrow     - Go forward
• Ctrl + G              - Go to line number

Search & Replace
---------------
• Ctrl + F              - Find
• Ctrl + Shift + F      - Find in all files
• Ctrl + H              - Replace
• Ctrl + Shift + H      - Replace in all files
• F3                    - Find next match
• Shift + F3            - Find previous match

Code Folding
------------
• Ctrl + Shift + [      - Fold region
• Ctrl + Shift + ]      - Unfold region
• Ctrl + K Ctrl + 0     - Fold all
• Ctrl + K Ctrl + J     - Unfold all

File/Window Management
---------------------
• Ctrl + N              - New file
• Ctrl + Tab            - Switch between open files
• Ctrl + W              - Close current file
• Ctrl + \              - Split editor
• Ctrl + B              - Toggle sidebar

Quick Actions
------------
• Ctrl + Shift + P      - Show command palette
• Ctrl + .              - Quick fix/suggestions
• F2                    - Rename symbol
• Alt + Shift + F       - Format document

Most Used Professional Shortcuts
------------------------------
• Home/End              - Line navigation
• Ctrl + Left/Right     - Word navigation
• Ctrl + D              - Selecting occurrences
• Alt + Up/Down         - Moving lines
• Ctrl + Shift + K      - Deleting lines
• F12                   - Go to definition

Note: These shortcuts are based on VS Code/Cursor defaults. Most modern IDEs follow similar patterns.